CLOUD COMPUTING (CLOUD VS ON-PREM)
Cloud Modals 
1.Convenient
2.On-demand
3.Ubiquitous
4.Network access (Servers, Storage)

Cloud provides rapid responsiveness when deploying services to customers.
The cloud uses utility approach (pay as you go pricing)
The cloud architect is easy in setting up other than traditional architectures.

FEATURES OF THE CLOUD

Shared resources pooling (you can access any resources without knowing where it came from or the provider.)
Measured service (measure the  various service you use or being used. )
Rapid elasticity (provide as many services and resources you need at anytime.)
Self-service (On-demand).(Anyone can setup any service at any moment without the assistant of a technical expert.)
Network Access (Access from anywhere at any giving time.)
